      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:7:4:44:2",
      "text": [
        "هُ قَالَ فِي رَجُلٍ كَانَ جَالِساً مَعَ قَوْمٍ فَمَاتَ وَ هُوَ مَعَهُمْ أَوْ رَجُلٍ وُجِدَ فِي قَبِيلَةٍ أَوْ عَلَى بَابِ دَارِ قَوْمٍ فَادُّعِيَ عَلَيْهِمْ قَالَ لَيْسَ عَلَيْهِمْ شَيْ‏ءٌ وَ لَا يَبْطُلُ دَمُهُ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Muhammad Bin Yahya, from Ahmad Bin Muhammad, from Ali Bin Al Hakam, from Aban, from Muhammad Bin Muslim, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> having said regarding a man who was seated with a group of people, so he died and he was with them, or a man was found (dead) among his tribe, or upon a door of a people, so it was claimed against them. He<sup>asws</sup> said: ‘There is nothing upon them, nor would his blood be invalidated’."
        ]
      }
    }
